{{Location map-line|lat=74}}
{{kml}}
The '''74th parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 74 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]], in the [[Arctic]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Europe]], [[Asia]], the [[Arctic Ocean]], and [[North America]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 74° north passes through:

