[[File:Campus Geesseknäppchen.jpg|thumb|Campus Geesseknäppchen]] '''Campus Geesseknäppchen''' is a [[campus]] in [[Luxembourg City]], in southern [[Luxembourg]], that is shared by a number of academic institutions.
The campus is located in the southwest of the city, just to the north of the terminus of the [[A4 road (Luxembourg)|A4]] [[motorway]]. It is predominantly in the [[Quarters of Luxembourg City|quarter]] of [[Hollerich]], although the western part (including the [[Conservatoire de Luxembourg|Conservatoire]]) lies in [[Merl, Luxembourg|Merl]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vdl.lu/Mairie+et+services+centraux/Urbanisme/D%C3%A9veloppement+urbain/Stadtteilrahmenpl%C3%A4ne/Hollerich-highlight-hollerich-p-3700672.html|title=Stadtentwicklungsplan Hollerich|accessdate=2008-03-31|last=|first=|date=|work=|publisher=Ville de Luxembourg|language=de}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Shaped roughly like a [[right triangle]], the campus measures 800 metres (880 [[yard]]s) east-west along the [[hypotenuse]], and {{convert|520|m|yd|abbr=off}} north-south at its maximum.
Geesseknäppchen is the site of:
* [[Athénée de Luxembourg]] * [[Conservatoire de Luxembourg]] * [[International School of Luxembourg]] * [[Lycée Aline Mayrisch]] * [[Lycée Michel Rodange]] * [[Lycée Technique Ecole de Commerce et de Gestion]]
The campus has shared sporting facilities, including an athletics track, five sports halls, an [[Olympic size swimming pool]], and a [[football (soccer)|football]] (soccer) pitch.
The Japanese Supplementary School in Luxembourg (ルクセンブルグ補習授業校 ''Rukusenburugu Hoshū Jugyō Kō''), a [[hoshuko|Japanese supplementary school]],<ref name=MEXTEuropeHoshuko>"[http://www.mext.go.jp/a_menu/shotou/clarinet/002/006/001/002/004.htm 欧州の補習授業校一覧（平成25年4月15日現在）]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6PT4aGXC8?url=http://www.mext.go.jp/a_menu/shotou/clarinet/002/006/001/002/004.htm Archive]). [[Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology]] (MEXT). Retrieved on May 10, 2014.</ref> is held at ISL. Its operations began there in 1991 and it serves students ages 6–15.<ref name=ExpatriateJapaneseRussian>"[http://www.wort.lu/en/community/how-expatriate-children-stay-in-touch-with-their-cultural-roots-supplementary-schools-in-luxembourg-531d6e1ce4b03e321374f515 How expatriate children stay in touch with their cultural roots - supplementary schools in Luxembourg]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6WLvUB39h?url=http://www.wort.lu/en/community/how-expatriate-children-stay-in-touch-with-their-cultural-roots-supplementary-schools-in-luxembourg-531d6e1ce4b03e321374f515 Archive]). ''[[Luxemburger Wort]]''. Monday 10 March 2014. Retrieved on 14 February 2015.</ref>
