{{short description|A marginal sea of the Southern Ocean, north of the coast of Adélie Land, East Antarctica}}
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
[[File:Antarctica.svg|thumb|upright=1.5|D'Urville Sea in Eastern Antarctica.]]

'''D'Urville Sea''' is a sea of the [[Southern Ocean]], north of the coast of [[Adélie Land]], [[East Antarctica]]. It is named after the French explorer and officer [[Jules Dumont d'Urville]].

{{coord|65|00|S|140|00|E|type:waterbody_source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}

