{{Infobox hotel | hotel_name = Hyatt Regency Lexington | image = Hyatt Regency Lexington.jpg | caption = | location = 401 West High Street, [[Lexington, Kentucky]], [[United States]], 40507 | opening_date = 1977
| diamonds = | closing_date = | architect = | developer = | operator = | owner = | number_of_restaurants = 2 | number_of_rooms = 366 | number_of_suites = | floor_area = | floors = 17 | parking = | website = http://lexington.regency.hyatt.com/en/hotel/home.html | footnotes = }}
The '''Hyatt Regency Lexington''' is a 17-story, 366-room [[hotel]] located in [[Lexington, Kentucky]]. It opened in 1977 and is 190 feet (58 meters) in height. The hotel is located adjacent to [[Rupp Arena]].<ref>[http://lexington.regency.hyatt.com/en/hotel/home.html Hyatt Regency Lexington] Official Website. Retrieved on 2010-09-24</ref>
==Building Facts== It was designed by firms Ellerbe & Company and JR Architect.<ref>[http://www.emporis.com/application/?lng=3&nav=building&id=127927 Hyatt Rengency Lexington] Emporis. Retrieved on 2010-09-24</ref> Precast prestressed concrete planks were used as the flooring system. The tower structure utilizes 56 Pratt-type trusses, each 60 feet long, in a staggered configuration. The hotel contains a seven-story atrium; the glass roof is supported by a space frame.
