==Awards==
Wooldridge received a number of awards to fund fieldwork, including the Royal Geographical Society's [[Murchison Award]] with [[David Leslie Linton|David Linton]] in 1942. He was made [[CBE]] in 1954 in recognition of his work on the Sand and Gravel Council. In 1957 he received the Royal Geographical Society's [[Victoria Medal (geography)|Victoria Medal]] and in 1959 was elected a [[Fellow of the Royal Society]], a rare honour among geographers.<ref name=baigent />

